<span style="color: gray; display: block; vertical-align: top;"><span style="color: #333333; display: block;">**<span style="color: #3b5998; text-decoration: none;">[[https://www.facebook.com/shervin/posts/10150470194461549|Shervin Pishevar]]:</span>**</span>Diplomacy devoid of discretion ceases to be diplomacy. We've entered a new transparent world I call Transplomacy- or open sourced diplomacy. Transplomacy is a new path nations can take embracing our new real-time, transparent world. [[TransPlomacy]] accepts that in a real time world secrets have ever faster expiration date<span class="text_exposed_show">s going forward. Transplomacy recognizes the conundrum that the faster secrets are revealed the faster the rate of conflicts in the world. Transplomacy solves this conundrum by embracing openness. A world run in the bright light of day keeps out shadows where evil and conflict can fester. Let me know if I should write a piece about Transplomacy being a new way forward for 21st Century Diplomacy. If you have thoughts please share.</span>
